In [[Greek mythology]], '''Hegetoria''' was a local [[nymph]] at [[Rhodes]] who married [[Ochimus]]. They had a daughter, [[Cydippe]] or Cyrbia, who married Ochimus's brother, [[Cercaphus]], successor to his brother's power.<ref>[[Diodorus Siculus]], ''Library of History'' 5.57.7</ref> According to an alternate version, Ochimus engaged Cydippe to [[Ocridion]] but Cercaphus loved her and kidnapped her. He did not return until Ochimus was old.<ref>[[Plutarch]], ''Quaestiones Graecae'', 27</ref>

